<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10077e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10077e">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10077e"> 77(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> mutations / mansion</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Les relais &eacute;tablis par le gouvernement r&eacute;publicain sur les routes militaires avaient re&ccedil;u originairement le nom de positiones, (stations); ensuite, on les divisa en trois classes: 1&deg; civitates ou cit&eacute;s; 2&deg; <mark>mutationes</mark> ou lieux de changements; 3&deg; <mark>mansiones</mark>, ou lieux de halte. <font color="green">[The relays established by the republican government along military roads were originally called by the name positiones (stations). Later they were divided into three classes: 1) civitates or cities; 2) mutationes or changing posts; and 3) mansiones or stopping stations.]</font> <small> Arthur de Rothschild, <a name="ARHD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ARHD"><cite title="source">Histoire de la poste</cite></a> (1876) 38</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
